Instruction to install the smonitor daemon on Ubuntu (tested on Ubuntu Server 12.04)

We suppose, you have already download smonitor files from github
git clone https://github.com/ifke/smonitor.git
and come in the folder of the program
cd smonitor

1. Import to your zabbix server the template contrib/zbx_template_smonitor.xml, bind it to switches and acvite/disable items hosts_on_port[X] according to the number of ports of each switch

2. Install necessary utilities and python modules
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install python-daemon snmp arp-scan zabbix-agent

3. Create the user for daemon running
sudo useradd --create-home --system --comment "smonitor daemon" --shell /bin/false smonitor

4. Copy python files of the program to the home folder of the new user
sudo cp -v *.py /home/smonitor

5. Set settings of the daemon in file /home/smonitor/Settings.py

6. Configure attributes of the arp-scan file
sudo chown root:smonitor /usr/bin/arp-scan
sudo chmod 4750 /usr/bin/arp-scan

7. Check parameters of the init script in contrib/smonitr and copy it to the folder /etc/init.d
sudo cp contrib/smonitor /etc/init.d

8. Run smonitor in debug mode
/home/smonitor/smonitor.py --debug

9. If your zabbix server have get data successfully, stop the program pressing Ctrl-C and run it as a daemon
sudo /etc/init.d/smonitor start
if program works properly in debug mode, but doesn't start as a daemon, most likely it can't create the pid file.
Check the user and the path to the file in the init script, so the pidfile parameter in the Settings.py file.

10. Configure autostart of the daemon
sudo update-rc.d smonitor defaults
